	" Game objectives
	$LF
]h3
[ul 
	[li 
		" Emulator used: VBA-rr v23.6 svn480
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Aims for fastest input time.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Abuses programming errors in the game.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Manipulates luck.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Takes damage to save time.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Uses glitched warps.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Corrupts memory.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Skips final boss.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[h3 id=DoesthisTASreachanending? 
	" Does this TAS reach an ending?
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Yes, as seen in the last part of the run.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=ButdoesthisTASreallybeatthegame? 
	" But does this TAS really beat the game?
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Yes, since it reaches the ENDING and unlocks in SRAM new modes that are only for getting the Good Ending.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=Branchoftherun? 
	" Branch of the run?
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"This run can be compared to the Castlevania: Dawn of Sorrow "any%" run. I consider this to be a "glitch-warped any% with memory corruptions".
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"See the Glitches below for technical details.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=WhynotBadEnding? 
	" Why not Bad Ending?
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Conventionally we are always speedrunning the Metroidvania Castlevania series for the Good Endings (aka. True Endings according to the storyline instead of the Bad Endings that are considered "incomplete"), which are best suited for the Moons.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=But... 
	" But...
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"And Good Ending is actually faster to achieve in this TAS with the glitches.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=Comments 
	" Comments
	$LF
]h3
[h4 id=Glitches 
	" Glitches
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"For other glitches used in the run, see the Game Resources 
	[a class=intlink href=/GameResources/GBx/CastlevaniaAriaOfSorrow 
		"article
	]a
	".
	$LF
]div
[dl 
	[dt 
		"SLEEP Warp
	]dt
	[dd 
		$LF
	]dd
]dl
[div class=p 
	"The address 0x0200009E keep tracks on which room the game would resume from a suspended game with the SLEEP feature. 
	$LF
	"This SLEEP room number can be treated as a whole 16-bit value, whose low 8-bit byte represents which area Soma is in, 
	$LF
	"and high 8-bit byte represents which room in the area Soma is in. 
	$LF
	"(Alternatively, you may treat the low byte and high byte as two separate values, which doen't affect the points here.)
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"By going out-of-bound under the 0HP status, it is possible to set bits at 0x0200009E. 
	$LF
	"Simply with proper calculation, this can be abused to allow SLEEP-Warp from the current room to other rooms located at higher addresses in the ROM.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The ending event object is only placed in Room SLEEP No. 0x280B. Thanks to out-of-range reading, an equivalent SLEEP No. for the same room can be 0xCF05, 0x9D07 etc.. 
	$LF
	"I am aiming for getting 0xCF05 in this run, as this value can be easily made from the big rooms in Floating Garden with the rush-OoB method, 
	$LF
	"while the other possible starting points require Giant Bat to get OoB with 0HP or are simply too far away from 0x0200009E on the castle map.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Since the SLEEP Room address is outside supposed memory range of the castle map, I regard this exploit as memory corruption.
	$LF
]div
[dl 
	[dt 
		"Ending event trigger
	]dt
	[dd 
		$LF
	]dd
]dl
[div class=p 
	"The ending event in the room always triggers as soon as the room is loaded with Soma's HP > 0. 
	$LF
	"If Soma's HP = 0 when this room is loaded, the ending event won't be triggered and the room is glitched. 
	$LF
	"It is still possible to SLEEP again, and the event can be triggered if Soma's HP > 0 the next time the game is resumed, 
	$LF
	"as if is were the first time.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Since the ending event in the room is triggered in the designed way, I consider this run to be a "glitch-warped" rather than "ending-glitched".
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=Soulsusedintherun 
	" Souls used in the run
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Red Souls = "Bullet" Souls, Blue Souls = "Guardian" Souls, Yellow Souls = "Enhancement" Souls, Silver Souls = "Ability" Souls.
	$LF
]div
[dl 
	[dt 
		"Winged Skeleton
	]dt
	[dd 
		$LF
	]dd
]dl
[div class=p 
	"A Red Soul with high attack power at low MP cost. Automatically obtained and equipped in the beginning of the quest.
	$LF
]div
[dl 
	[dt 
		"Grave Keeper
	]dt
	[dd 
		$LF
	]dd
]dl
[div class=p 
	"A Silver Soul that enables back-dashes. It allows faster movements than simply walking and is easy to obtain from the latern in the mermen in front of the first saveroom.
	$LF
]div
[dl 
	[dt 
		"Killer Fish
	]dt
	[dd 
		$LF
	]dd
]dl
[div class=p 
	"A Red Soul with high attack power at low MP cost. It can cover a long range but can only be used underwater.
	$LF
]div
[dl 
	[dt 
		"Giant Worm
	]dt
	[dd 
		$LF
	]dd
]dl
[div class=p 
	"A Yellow Soul which restores Soma's HP by 5 point every 60 frames when Soma has zero horizontal momentum and performing no attacks. 
	$LF
	"The in-game menu will reset this timer.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The HP regeneration occurs right before the checks of the game logic for room transitions, 
	$LF
	"leaving no chance to enter the in-game menu between the HP regeneration and room transition. 
	$LF
	"As a result, this Soul can't be used to recover HP for the particular SLEEP-Warp to the ending event room.
	$LF
]div
[dl 
	[dt 
		"Ukoback
	]dt
	[dd 
		$LF
	]dd
]dl
[div class=p 
	"A Red Soul with good attack power at low MP cost. It has Fire attribute, making it especially powerful against certain enemies.
	$LF
]div
[dl 
	[dt 
		"Killer Mantle
	]dt
	[dd 
		$LF
	]dd
]dl
[div class=p 
	"A Red Soul with OK attack power at OK MP cost. It can modify certain enemies' HP for once, killing them or making them tougher.
	$LF
]div
[dl 
	[dt 
		"Hippogriff
	]dt
	[dd 
		$LF
	]dd
]dl
[div class=p 
	"A Silver Soul that enables infinite high-jumps. Required for getting to high places and fast for vertical/diagonal travelling.
	$LF
]div
[dl 
	[dt 
		"Iron Golem
	]dt
	[dd 
		$LF
	]dd
]dl
[div class=p 
	"A Yellow Soul which allows Soma to take damage without interrupting his movements. 
	$LF
	"However, it is only used in this run as a way to perform the 0HP glitch but never equipped.
	$LF
]div
[dl 
	[dt 
		"Curly
	]dt
	[dd 
		$LF
	]dd
]dl
[div class=p 
	"A Blue Soul with high attack power. However it is only used as a movement assitant and wall-zipping method.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"During the stuck-in-place frames when using Curly allows the timer of Giant Worm Soul to tick on, 
	$LF
	"making these two an interesting combination.
	$LF
]div
[dl 
	[dt 
		"Dead Warrior
	]dt
	[dd 
		$LF
	]dd
]dl
[div class=p 
	"A Yellow Soul that allows Soma to override normal main-weapon attacks with equipped Red Soul's attack. 
	$LF
	"The description in the (U) version is just a mis-translation.
	$LF
]div
