	" First castle room
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Nothing to help with the long opening dialogue. The subpixel adjustment on the slope helps later.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=CastleCorridor 
	" Castle Corridor
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Baselard is obtained from the Zombie as in other CVAoS TASes. 
	$LF
	"The unnecessary Tunic Cloth as seen in the previous run is skipped this time, 
	$LF
	"for its presence in the inventory would cause extra lags in the body-equipment menu.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=Mermen-infestedroomandsaveroom 
	" Mermen-infested room and saveroom
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"The nightmare room for luck manipulation. It's easier this time as I don't need farming EXP from Mermen any more. 
	$LF
	"Still the damage boost after saving relies on luck and I think I've got the optimal outcome.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"As usual, Grave Keeper Soul is aquired for faster movements and Causual Cloth is unequipped for taking more damage.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=UndergroundReservoir 
	" Underground Reservoir
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"The Tiny Devil is utilized for reducing some HP and getting a Mind Up. 
	$LF
	"Then the Skeleton. Its air-juggling attacks contributes to some damage too. 
	$LF
	"Following them are the Killer Fishes to hurt Soma more. 
	$LF
	"The first one gives a piece of Tasty Meat and the second one presents its soul for the first application of the 0HP glitch.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Now SLEEP and....
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=1stContinue 
	" 1st Continue
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Showtime!
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Unseen hard part: to avoid rolling on the PRNG as much as possible. 
	$LF
	"Using the Tasty Meat got just now starts wall-zipping and warping to....
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=LongshaftandGiantWormroominUndergroundReservoir 
	" Long shaft and Giant Worm room in Underground Reservoir
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"I need Giant Worm Soul here instead of a lot more HP-restoring items. 
	$LF
	"The PRNG window for Giant Worm Soul is pretty tight, but the fight is easy.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The Cagnazzo here may drop Onikiri, a weaker version of Kunitsuna. 
	$LF
	"The weapon is better than Baselard, however, 
	$LF
	"this Cagnazzo is surprisingly much more difficult to take down than its brothers versions, 
	$LF
	"as it keeps hovering over Soma's head like a mosquito until it finally decides to strike down, 
	$LF
	"which makes it a very much time-consuming oppenent without an overhead-swinging weapon. 
	$LF
	"However it is just ignored since I can rely on Baselard and Red Souls instead until I get the superior Kunitsuna in the next area.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Ukoback Soul is also used for 0HP here.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"SLEEP then....
	$LF
]div
