[h4 id=6thContinue 
	" 6th Continue
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Showtime!
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Nothing is hard with the movement. 
	$LF
	"The target map blocks that need to be explored to set the bits of 0x0200009E are divided to two parts. 
	$LF
	"The first part 0x0700 is directly reachable from the upper-left corner of this room, 
	$LF
	"and the second part 0x0C00 is separated from the first part by three blocks. 
	$LF
	"The optimal way to explore them all is to highjump diagonally to the first part, 
	$LF
	"fall down to the ground, go left, then highjump diagonally again to the second part, 
	$LF
	"as moving on the ground is overall faster than jumping in the air. 
	$LF
	"This is exactly what is done in the run.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"However, the Giant Worm causes a little trouble here: 
	$LF
	"its effect is no longer needed, but its timer could just have enough ticks to regenerate 5 superfluous HP. 
	$LF
	"Either unquipping it or resetting its timer takes quite a few frames. 
	$LF
	"So what to do? Just use the Curly-backdash once less, which is merely 1-frame-worth.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The remaining MP is perfectly enough for this. No more, no less. ;)
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Time to SLEEP for the last time as soon as Soma hits the border pixel of the last block....
	$LF
]div
